## Creative diversity directly expands auction entry and reach

The fundamental shift post-Andromeda: **creative IS the targeting**. Different creative styles reach different audience segments automatically. Men in ads target men; technical tutorials reach education seekers; emotional stories reach narrative-driven buyers.

Advertisers report that diverse creative portfolios lower CPMs by increasing total addressable market. When Andromeda scans its hierarchical index, diverse creatives occupy multiple nodes, creating more "entry points" into auctions. Homogeneous creative restricts which user embeddings your ads can match, effectively limiting reach without manual targeting restrictions.

Five Nine Strategy's 45-day A/B test demonstrated this clearly. Traditional structure (1 campaign, 5 ad sets, 5 creatives each) saw 65% of budget concentrated on top 3 ads. Consolidated structure (1 campaign, 1 ad set, 25 diverse creatives) achieved **17% more conversions** and **16% lower cost per conversion**, with only 50% of budget going to top 3 ads—indicating better distribution and broader reach.

Meta's official data reinforces this: advertisers using Advantage+ Creative (which leverages Andromeda's matching) experienced a **22% increase in ROAS**.

