## What counts as meaningfully different versus redundant

**NOT meaningfully different (treated as same ad):**
- Same image with different colored backgrounds
- Same video with different headline text overlays  
- Same creator with same setup, different scripts
- Slight copy tweaks ("Save 20%" vs. "Get 20% Off")
- Same model in similar environments

**Meaningfully different (Andromeda rewards):**
- Founder story video vs. customer testimonial vs. product demo
- Problem-focused pain point ad vs. aspirational lifestyle ad
- Technical demonstration vs. emotional transformation story
- Professional studio content vs. authentic UGC
- Static image vs. video vs. carousel
- Different models/creators in different environments

The practical test: would these ads appeal to different people for different reasons? If yes, they're distinct. If they're the same concept with surface-level variations, Andromeda clusters them.

