## Multiple creative styles in one ad set: confirmed to work

**The answer to your core question is unambiguously YES.** Putting founder POV, demo, UGC, CGC, and walkthrough creatives inside ONE ad set works with Andromeda, not against it.

"When you produce varied creative tailored to different personas and pain points, Andromeda automatically matches each ad with the right users. Now, your ads are your targeting." This is the consensus across Smart Marketer, Foxwell Digital, Five Nine Strategy, and multiple agency reports.

Andromeda will retrieve different styles to different micro-audiences automatically because it maps both users and creatives into the same embedding space. A founder story ad occupies different coordinates than a technical demo—and matches different user profiles. Your concept-bucket approach gives Andromeda more "surface area" to find matches across diverse audience segments who care about the same underlying value proposition but respond to different creative languages.

**One caveat: monitor for "Hot Ad Bias."** Andromeda can identify a "winner" within hours and allocate 90%+ of budget to that single asset. If this happens, consider isolating starved creatives into a new ad set or applying cost caps to force diversification. But this is a tuning issue, not a structural flaw—the consolidated approach still outperforms fragmented campaigns.

