## Conclusion: Your belief-led strategy aligns with Andromeda's architecture

Your proposed approach—validate market beliefs with static "probes," then graduate winners into multi-style creative expansion inside concept-bucket ad sets—is precisely how Andromeda is designed to work. The retrieval system rewards accounts that provide diverse creative entry points for matching users across the embedding space.

The probe-to-expansion workflow efficiently tests concepts before committing production resources, and the concept-bucket structure (one validated concept expressed through founder POV, demo, UGC, CGC, walkthrough) maximizes both retrieval eligibility and audience reach. Critically, keeping styles together in one ad set prevents data fragmentation while giving Andromeda the variety it needs to personalize delivery.

The evidence suggests **8-15 distinct creative expressions per validated concept** as the optimal range for staying "retrieval-rich" without overwhelming learning capacity. Refresh cycles of 2-4 weeks will prevent fatigue while maintaining momentum. And the most important shift: stop thinking about targeting and start thinking about which creative languages will resonate with different buyer psychologies. Andromeda handles the matching—you just need to give it enough diverse material to work with.